Bradley Hansell has been nominated to be the Deputy Under Secretary of Defense for Intelligence and Security. He is currently an Associate Director at Boston Consulting Group and has expertise in strategy. Hansell previously served as a Special Assistant to the President for National Security Affairs and was a Senior Director for Transnational Threats on the National Security Council staff. He has also worked as a Consultant at Boston Consulting Group's Washington, D.C. office. Hansell is a retired Army Special Forces Officer and has received awards for his service, including the Bronze Star, Purple Heart, and Meritorious Service Medal. He holds a B.A. from Villanova University and an MBA from the Darden Business School at the University of Virginia.

In addition, Michael Wynne has been nominated to be a Member of the Board of Visitors to the United States Air Force Academy, and Steven D. Poulin has been nominated to be the Joint Task Force East Director at the Department of Homeland Security.